{
  "id": "definite-articles",
  "title": "Definite Articles",
  "order": 2,
  "summary": "Catalan has four words for 'the', plus a contraction before vowels.",
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "English has one definite article: 'the'. Catalan has four, depending on the gender and number of the noun. There is also a special contracted form used before nouns starting with a vowel or silent h."
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "el gat",
          "english": "the cat (masculine singular)",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "la porta",
          "english": "the door (feminine singular)",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "els gats",
          "english": "the cats (masculine plural)",
          "note": ""
        },
        {
          "catalan": "les portes",
          "english": "the doors (feminine plural)",
          "note": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "content": "Before a noun starting with a vowel or silent h, 'el' and 'la' contract to 'l'': l'home (the man), l'aigua (the water). Els and les do not contract."
    },
    {
      "type": "examples",
      "items": [
        {
          "catalan": "l'home",
          "english": "the man",
          "note": "el + home → l'home"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "l'aigua",
          "english": "the water",
          "note": "la + aigua → l'aigua"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "l'estació",
          "english": "the station",
          "note": "la + estació → l'estació"
        },
        {
          "catalan": "els homes",
          "english": "the men",
          "note": "plural — no contraction"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Catalan also has a 'personal article' used before people's names in informal speech: en (masculine) and la/na (feminine). So a Catalan might say 'en Joan' or 'la Maria'. You'll hear this but don't need to worry about producing it yet."
    },
    {
      "type": "rule",
      "content": "To make a noun plural: nouns ending in a vowel add -s (porta → portes, gat → gats... wait, gat ends in a consonant). Nouns ending in a consonant add -s too: gat → gats, tren → trens."
    }
  ],
  "practice": [
